RACE.RACE_TEXT: AIKEN RACE 1 2 1/8M Hurdle CR: N/A. Maiden Claiming Purse 20000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 142 lbs.; Four Year Olds, 150 lbs.; Older, 154 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BELLARMINE HALL ran unhurried early, came off the pace to gain position after the 8th hurdle, moved to the inside to bid 3/8 from home, and assumed the lead in the stretch for the win. ABSAM kept pace with the early leader, assumed command after the 4th hurdle to lead the second circuit, was challenged in the stretch and just missed. SLEIGHT OF HAND raced middle of the pack through the 8th hurdle, bid before the last hurdle but faded in the stretch. SECRET SOULMATE rated at the back of the field for the first mile, gained position 3/8 from home, but was unable to make further gain in the stretch. THALEEQ (GB) rated and ran evenly, bid to gain position after the first mile, moved to contention 3/8 from home, could not sustain the bid and faded. KENYA ROAD kept the pace early through 6 hurdles, faded and pulled up before the last hurdle and walked off. SCOTTY led the first mile, tired and pulled up before the second to last hurdle and walked off.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AIKEN RACE 2 2 3/8M Hurdle CR: N/A. Handicap Purse 25000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH ARE RATED 115 OR LOWER, OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING $20,000. The highest rated horse will be assigned 158 lbs. with all other weights adjusted accordingly based on the current ratings. In the cas e of a horse entered for the price, the weight will be determined by current ratings and may exceed the 158 lb. highweight.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OSCAR WINNER went out to an early lead, settled behind rivals after the first half circuit, gained quickly on the inside approaching the final hurdle, entered the stretch in contention and prevailed for the win. TEASE AND SEIZE (FR) kept pace with the leaders through 8 hurdles, assumed the lead after the 9th hurdle, entered the stretch in the lead but was outrun to just miss. AGITARE (IRE) settled toward the back of the field early, ran evenly, bid before the final hurdle to gain position going into the stretch, but was unable to gain further on the leaders. EYE OF GUNFIGHTER assumed the lead after the first half mile to set the pace through the 8th hurdle, relinquished the lead at the second to last hurdle, and faded before the last hurdle. WICKED WEST (IRE) ran evenly at the back of the field through 7 hurdles, passed tiring rivals 3/8 from home, and was no threat. MET IN MIAMI ran in the back of the field, showed no speed, and was never a threat. ARROWHEART ran evenly in the middle of the pack, faded after the 7th hurdle, pulled up before the last hurdle and walked off. VINCENT VAN GOGO maintained position in the middle of the pack, fell at the 2nd to last hurdle and walked off. UNION GEN. GEORGE rated early, fell on the 4th hurdle, and walked off. The rider of WICKED WEST (IRE) lodged a claim of foul against the field. The field was waved around the 9th hurdle on the second circuit due to the previous fall of UNION GEN. GEORGE, and the rider claiming foul alleged that the rest of the field had gone off course. The stewards conducted an inquiry, and following the review, determined that all horses and riders made their best effort to safely return to the course. The claim of foul was disallowed and there was no change to the order of finish.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AIKEN RACE 3 2 1/8M Hurdle CR: N/A. Maiden Special Weight Purse 20000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $20,000 OR LESS ON THE FLAT, OR OVER FENCES. Three-year-olds, 142 lbs.; four-yearolds, 150 lbs.; older, 154 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: QUICK MASTER broke for the lead, set the pace throughout the race, was challenged at the top of the stretch and prevailed for the win. THE QUANTICO KID stalked the pace throughout, entered the stretch in contention, the rider lost his whip in the stretch, was hand-ridden to the wire and just missed. EVIE'S PRINCE settled toward the back of the field, ran evenly, and was no menace. SOUTHPAW MIKE rated, settled in the back, and was no threat. URBAN MYTH ran out the back, showed no speed, stumbled at the second to last hurdle and lost his rider after SAMUI SUNSET fell in front of him. SAMUI SUNSET kept the pace, dueled with THE QUANTICO KID between calls, fell at the second to last hurdle and walked off.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AIKEN RACE 4 2 1/8M Hurdle CR: N/A. Maiden Special Weight Purse 30000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 142 lbs.; Four Year Olds, 150 lbs.; Older, 154 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ACTIVE DUTY (FR) kept pace with the leaders, assumed command 3/8 from home, and drew away in the stretch for the win. KITTEN AROUND ran evenly the first mile, gained ground on the leaders after the 6th hurdle, and bid in the stretch to edge out the nearest rival for place. TRAVESURAS settled middle of the field in the early going, gained ground after the 7th hurdle to move to close contention with the leader, entered the stretch in contention but was outrun. MACHEEDA (IRE) started strong to keep pace with the leaders early, led briefly after the first circuit, began losing ground after the 8th hurdle, had no finishing speed and was eased home. GIANTSBANE started at the back of the field, ran evenly, passed tiring rivals, but was no threat and was eased home. JUST ANOTHER ONE (IRE) started well to set the early pace, faded quickly after the first mile, and pulled up before the last hurdle and walked off. ALL ROSES rated early, ran evenly, showed no speed, and pulled up before the last hurdle, and walked off. KENILWORTH KING settled middle of the pack early, assumed the lead after the 6th hurdle, began increasing the lead before the 7th hurdle, then cut sharply to the inside on the approach to the 7th hurdle, went through the inside wing, and went off course, losing the rider in the process. RIPTIDE ROCK broke slowly at the start, jumped poorly over the first three hurdles, and was pulled up before the 4th hurdle and walked off.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Holiday Cup S. AIKEN RACE 5 2 1/8M Hurdle CR: N/A. Stakes Purse 35000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES FOR THREE AND FOUR YEAR OLDS. Three-year-olds 140 lbs; four-year-olds 148 lbs. Winners, other claiming, 3 lbs. extra for each race won.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KIYOMORI assumed an early lead, set the pace, dueled briefly with TOTAL JOY (IRE) after the first circuit, and just outpaced TOTAL JOY (IRE) for the win. TOTAL JOY (IRE) stalked the pace, led between calls, pressed the pace after the 7th hurdle, bid in the stretch and just missed.
